<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph id="IFRS11_5" base="F16125391" principles="yes"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>5</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS&#xa0;11"/><data name="paranum" value="5"/></prolog><body outputclass="bold"><p id="IFRS11_P0020">A joint arrangement has the following characteristics: </p><ol outputclass="static" id="IFRS11_L0001" base="F16125393" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IFRS11_P0021" base="F16125394">The parties are bound by a contractual arrangement (see <xref id="IFRS11_X0068" base="F16217082" href="IFRS11_gB2-B4.dita#IFRS11_gB2-B4">paragraphs B2&#x2013;B4</xref>).</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IFRS11_P0022" base="F16125397">The contractual arrangement gives two or more of those parties joint control of the arrangement (see <xref id="IFRS11_X0069" base="F16217083" href="IFRS11_g7-13.dita#IFRS11_g7-13">paragraphs 7&#x2013;13</xref>).</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>